entral Idea: The ray will get transmitted through face <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mi>C</mi></math> if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>i</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>i</mi><mi>C</mi></msub></math></p><p>Consider the ray diagram is shown below.</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/c8caa2f8-5e6e-498a-8116-e0e837a24043-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 180px;\" /></p><p>A ray of light incident on face <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></math> at an angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo></math> Angle of refraction on face <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo></math> Angle of incidence at face <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mi>C</mi></math></p><p>For transmission of light through face <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mi>C</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>i</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>i</mi><mi>C</mi></msub></math></p><p>or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>i</mi><mi>C</mi></msub></math></p><p>or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>sin</mi><msub><mi>i</mi><mi>C</mi></msub></math></p><p>or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p>or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Now, applying Snell&#39;s law at the face&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>sin</mi><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></p><p>or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>sin</mi><mfenced close=\"}\" open=\"{\"><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": 